posts.title: Healthcare is up 314% since 1999
posts.author: WokeYoke

twitter.content:
Average US family health insurance premium...
1999: $6k
2002: $8k
2005: $11k
2008: $13k
2011: $15k
2014: $17k
2017: $19k
2020: $21k
2023: $24k

That's a 314% increase since 1999 (6.1% per year).

(Note: US CPI inflation has increased 2.5%/year)

posts.title: Should Harris be SELECTED, just as Biden was SELECTED... America as we knew it will end.
posts.content:
Should the SELECTIONS once again happen, and the will of the people be supplanted by the puppet masters, then the America as we knew it will have ended.

We are all aware, some more than others that our ability to choose our leaders no longer exists and it has been that way for some time now.

Should Trump not be named the winner of this upcoming election, there are many areas of our current nation that will be unable to accept the future that a Harris Presidency would bring.

The only option is State Secession.

There was a civil war in the past, no one should be worried about a civil war in the future. In order to have a civil war, there has to be TWO LARGE BODIES OF PEOPLE WHO ACTUALLY CARE ENOUGH TO FIGHT AN DIE.

In the above scenario, there is only ONE body of people that are willing to fight and die for their way of life. That body consists of The American Patriot, and those people hail from American States that still value the traditional American Way of Life.

Should Harris win, I encourage all Patriots to push for the exit from the United States of America's Federal Puppet Masters who reside in Washington D.C. I would even support all states leaving D.C. holding the bag of "national debt and all its self made problems", and all states re-federating under a new banner, free of D.C. influences.

The problem is not with America, or any State. The problem is the absolute CONTROL that Washington D.C. and its criminal cartels THINK they have over the states that permit them to play a role in our governance.

Either we win this election fairly, and Trump is ELECTED, or we end this charade of free and fair elections, and abandon the puppet masters to their little piece of land on our eastern coast of Virginia.
